ge has broken down rather than a standalone legal claim\n\n**Nuances:**\n\n- Courts typically require the withholding to be **unreasonable** and **prolonged**\u2014not temporary periods or negotiable differences in libido\n- Medical incapacity (illness, disability) generally doesn't count\u2014relevant to the coma discussion\n- Some jurisdictions require evidence the refusing spouse was **willful** in the deprivation\n- Religious marriage contracts sometimes include explicit \"conjugal rights\" provisions, enforceable in religious courts (Islamic law, some Jewish law contexts)\n\n**Notable:** The concept of \"marital duties\" including sex is ingrained in older legal frameworks, though modern law increasingly treats sex as something that must be willingly given rather than owed.", "embedding": [-0.06716285645961761, 0.018561283126473427, 0.013880979269742966, 0.08406728506088257, 0.020956693217158318, 0.030542412772774696, 0.010032846592366695, -0.04822181910276413, 0.031554967164993286, 0.03704904392361641, 0.028107643127441406, 0.012939213775098324, -0.011546396650373936, 0.0384347029030323, 0.07390415668487549, -0.008019844070076942, 0.11159547418355942, -0.06283701956272125, 0.01787756383419037, 0.1529051661491394, 0.04270569607615471, 0.03296540305018425, 0.017459051683545113, -0.004183058626949787, 0.0334661565721035, -0.029659636318683624, -0.021476024761795998, -0.03702274709939957, -0.025584453716874123, 0.008693180978298187, -0.023960376158356667, 0.11354508250951767, 0.01992199197411537, -0.003358703339472413, -0.03874043747782707, -0.0018389190081506968, -0.03641209378838539, 0.02805216610431671, -0.032290395349264145, -0.015552472323179245, -0.015083052217960358, -0.011573243886232376, 0.05861121788620949, -0.0010977324564009905, -0.061455801129341125, -0.024245673790574074, -0.0189287718385458, -0.0689314752817154, -0.051687199622392654, -0.03605249896645546, -0.04083866998553276, 0.05079321563243866, 0.04101245105266571, 0.15024733543395996, 0.0231241